title: Monster Energy Series drivers with multiple Western Swing wins

organizations.name: phoenix raceway and auto club speedway

text: Mar 21, 2017 at 1:07p ET 0Shares Believe it or not, there are only nine active drivers who’ve won multiple Monster Energy NASCAR Cup Series races at the three tracks that comprise NASCAR’s Western Swing: Las Vegas Motor Speedway, Phoenix Raceway and Auto Club Speedway. With the two races already in the books, the Western Swing will conclude with Sunday’s Auto Club 400 (FOX, 3 p.m. ET). Here are the nine drivers who’ve won multiple Western Swing races: 9. Ryan Newman, 2 Fresh off his stunning late-race run to victory at Phoenix on Sunday, Newman has two Western Swing wins, both at Phoenix. © Russell LaBounty/LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty 9. Kasey Kahne, 2 The Hendrick Motorsports driver won at Auto Club in 2006, when he drove a Ray Evernham-owned Dodge, and at Phoenix in 2011 in a Red Bull Toyota. Getty Images Getty Images for NASCAR 9. Kurt Busch, 2 The elder Busch won at Auto Club in 2003 and in Phoenix two years later. Getty Images Getty Images 5. Dale Earnhardt Jr., 3 All three of Earnhardt’s Western Swing victories have come at Phoenix, most recently in November 2015. Getty Images Getty Images 5. Brad Keselowski, 3 The Team Penske driver captured the 2015 race at Auto Club and won at Las Vegas in 2014 and ’16. Doug Pensinger 4. Kyle Busch, 5 A winner at all three Western Swing tracks, Busch will be one of the favorites this week at Auto Club, where he already has three victories. NASCAR NASCAR via Getty Images 3. Matt Kenseth, 7 Another driver to look out for this weekend is Kenseth, who has three wins each at Auto Club and Vegas, and one in Phoenix. Getty Images Getty Images 2. Kevin Harvick, 10 With eight wins at Phoenix, Harvick has showed exceptional dominance at that track. The 2014 champ also has won once each at Las Vegas and Auto Club. Getty Images Chris Graythen 1. Jimmie Johnson, 14 As you would expect, Johnson has posted some remarkable victory totals on the Western Swing, winning six times at Auto Club and four times each at Las Vegas and Phoenix. Getty Images Robert Laberge
